 on a roll with Out in the City/Out a Montreal|last=April 15|first=Playback Staff|last2=2002|access-date=2019-10-20}}</ref>\n|Lead Editor\n|90 minute\ndocumentary\n\n''(LIFE)''\n|\n|-\n|2002\n|''Cirque for Life'' <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cinemapolitica.org/artists/luc-c%C3%B4t%C3%A9|title=Luc C\u00f4t\u00e9|last=H2V 1H8Canada|first=Les Films Adobe Inc 70 St-Cyril Montreal|website=cinema politica|language=en|access-date=2019-10-14}}</ref>\n|Editor\n|52 minute\ndocumentary\n\n''(CBC, LIFE)''\n|\n|-\n|2002\n|She Got Game <ref>{{Citation|last=www.oberon.nl|first=Oberon Amsterdam|title=She Got Game: Behind the Scenes of the Women's Tennis Tour {{!}} IDFA|url=https://www.idfa.nl/en/film/8124abd4-a341-4023-91e3-3159f0fcc2df/she-got-game-behind-the-scenes-of-the-womens-tennis-tour|access-date=2019-11-02}}</ref>\n|Editor\n|90 minute\ndocumentary\n\n''(CBC, LIFE, TVO, TVQ)''\n| -Gold Aurora Award.\n-Guirlande d\u2019Honneur, Sports\n\nMovies & TV Int. Festival, Milan.\n\n-Best Documentary, [[Temecula Valley International Film Festival|Temecula]]\n\n[[Temecula Valley International Film Festival|Valley Int. Film and Music]]\n\n[[Temecula Valley International Film Festival|Festival]], California.\n\n-Chris Statuette, [[Columbus International Film & Video Festival|Columbus]]\n\n[[Columbus International Film & Video Festival|International Film Festival]].\n\n-Recognized by the [[International Olympic Committee|International]]\n\n[[International Olympic Committee|Olympic Committee]], FICTS\n\n(Federation Internationale\n\nCinema Television Sportif); Milan\n\n(2003).\n|-\n|2004\n|''Unbreakable Minds'' <ref name=\"Culture Unplugged\" />\n|Editor, Writer\n|56 minute\ndocumentary\n\n''(Vision)''\n|\n|-\n|2005\n|''Vendetta Song'' <ref name=\"nfb.ca\" />\n|Editor, Writer, Camera\n|52 minute\ndocumentary\n\n''(NFB, Vision)''\n|  -CIDA Prize for Best Canadian Documentary on International Development at [[Hot Docs Canadian International Documentary Festival|Hot Docs]] 2005 Quebec Fil